Reference-contexts: PARALLEL ALGORITHMS CCM2 incorporates two major dynamics algorithms: the spectral transform method (Eliasen, Machenhauer, and Rasmussen 1970; Orszag 1970) and semi-Lagrangian transport <ref> (Williamson and Rasch 1989) </ref>. The spectral transform method is used for the approximation of all terms in the equations except for the advective term in the moisture transport equation, which is updated using a semi-Lagrangian transport method. The spectral transform proceeds in two stages.
