Reference-contexts: The latter operation is achieved using a parallel vector sum algorithm (Drake et al. 1993); other algorithms have been found to be slightly more efficient in some cases, but are harder to integrate into PCCM2 <ref> (Worley and Drake 1992) </ref>. The semi-Lagrangian transport method used in CCM2 updates the value of the moisture field at a grid point (the arrival point, A) by first establishing a trajectory through which the particle arriving at A has moved during the current timestep.
